If you select 'bad' files to be imported, the importer will return you to the same page with an error message, but your selections will all be lost. Ideally these should be retained.

Additionally, the error message, e.g.
{quote}
This archive doesn't contains any valid JIRA Export file
{quote}
should reference the actual file name, e.g.
{quote}
This archive "myfile.zip" doesn't contain a valid JIRA export file
{quote}
(Note also the grammatical fixes.) This will help identify why the file is problematic if the user selected the wrong one by mistake.

Replicated on Chrome 28.0.1500.72 m

A User logs in JIRA and checks the "Keep Logged me in" checkbox. After closing the browser, the user then re-opens the browser using a direct link to one of his saved filters, JIRA displays an error message saying that the user is not logged in:

{quote}
(!) The requested filter doesn't exist or is private. Try logging in.
{quote}

If the user then clicks on the *JIRA* icon in the top left corner he is logged in automatically. This problem doesn't seem to happen if the user opens the browser on one of the system built-in filters or on the main dashboard.
